<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="64" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Willis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Honolulu</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-05-08"><hi rend="italic">May 8, 1895</hi></date>.
                                (Received May 1.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 109.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The British Government has just announced
                            its decision as to the citizenship of W. H. Ricard, T. B. Walker, and A.
                            M. Hewett, according to which the first two mentioned, not having
                            voluntarily and knowingly renounced their British citizenship or
                            received certificates of naturalization here, are held to be entitled to
                            the protection of their native country. Mr. Hewett’s claim to British
                            nationality is denied, as he had complied with all the conditions and
                            had accepted a certificate of Hawaiian nationality.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Albert S. Willis.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>